  n=5: α₁ mod 3 distribution: {0: 451, 1: 335, 2: 238}
  n=5: α₁ mod 4 distribution: {0: 428, 1: 273, 2: 203, 3: 120}
  n=5: α₁ mod 5 distribution: {0: 366, 1: 238, 2: 201, 3: 120, 4: 99}
  n=5: α₁ mod 6 distribution: {0: 331, 1: 236, 2: 201, 3: 120, 4: 99, 5: 37}
  n=6: α₁ mod 2 distribution: {0: 17544, 1: 15224}
  n=6: α₁ mod 3 distribution: {0: 11716, 1: 11031, 2: 10021}
  n=6: α₁ mod 4 distribution: {0: 9821, 1: 8467, 2: 7723, 3: 6757}
  n=6: α₁ mod 5 distribution: {0: 7780, 1: 6972, 2: 6790, 3: 5909, 4: 5317}
  n=6: α₁ mod 6 distribution: {0: 6629, 1: 6308, 2: 6192, 3: 5087, 4: 4723, 5: 3829}

So α₁ mod 2: NOT always 0 (both parities appear).
This means I(CG, 2) mod 4 is NOT always 1.
Confirmed: H mod 4 ∈ {1, 3}, determined by α₁ parity.

